&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-ratification/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-ratification/> ;
  schema:name "Ratification" ;
  schema:description "A Ratification is a triple (O, a, ρ) — an authorizing office O, an act a performed without O's prior authorization, and a ratification declaration ρ by which O retrospectively settles a's propositional content into H*_{t*}. The defining structure: ratification applies σ_{t*} ex post facto to a proposition φ ∈ H_{t*}  H*_{t*} — the act's content was not settled at the time of performance but becomes settled by the ratification declaration. The act a is then treated as having been authorized from the moment of performance: the Hohfeldian liability that attached to the unauthorized actor dissolves, and the obligations created by the act become binding on O. Formally: a nucleus application σ_{t*}(φ) = φ triggered not by the performance of a but by O's subsequent declaration." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:isPartOf &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/> ;
  schema:about &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-ratification/> ;
  rdfs:seeAlso "Authority, Investiture, Delegation, Breach, HohfeldianPosition, Act, StatusFunctionDeclaration, Contract" ;
